4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT CREATING A SENIOR CITIZEN CENTER GRANT PROGRAM TO
5 FUND CAPITAL CONSTRUCTION, MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR PROJECTS, AND EQUIPMENT
6 PURCHASES; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; ALLOWING APPROPRIATIONS TO CONTINUE INTO
7 THE 2027 AND 2029 BIENNIUMS; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND A TERMINATION DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Definitions. For the purposes of [sections 1 through 6], unless otherwise
12 provided, the following definitions apply:
13 (1) "Senior citizen" means a person over 60 years of age.
14 (2) (a) "Senior citizen center" means a facility operated by a nonprofit corporation or a
15 governmental organization that provides services to senior citizens in the form of daytime or evening meals,
16 educational programs, or recreational activities. Services qualifying under this definition must be recognized in
17 the state plan on aging adopted by the department of public health and human services.
18 (b) The term does not include a facility that provides living accommodations to senior citizens.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Senior citizen center infrastructure account -- use. (1) There is a
21 senior citizen center infrastructure account within the state special revenue fund provided for in 17-2-102 to
22 provide grant funding to nonprofit corporations that provide services to senior citizens and for administrative
23 costs related to administering the grants. The department of commerce shall administer the account.
24 (2) Up to 3% of the funds appropriated in [section 8] may be allocated for the department's
25 administrative costs.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Senior citizen center infrastructure grants authorization. (1) The
28 department of commerce is authorized to make up to $5 million in grants to nonprofit corporations for property
