1 acquisition, construction, space acquisition, remodeling, repairs, and the purchase of appliances and
2 equipment. The grants authorized in this section are subject to the conditions set forth in [section 5].
3 (2) The department of commerce must receive proposals from nonprofit corporations for senior
4 citizen center infrastructure projects.
5 (3) Funding for projects may be provided only as long as there are sufficient funds available from
6 the amount that was deposited or transferred in the senior citizen center infrastructure account for grants
7 established in [section 2]. Funding for these projects must be made available in the order that the grant
8 recipients satisfy the conditions described in [section 5].
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Eligibility -- submission deadline -- priority -- guidelines. (1) A
11 nonprofit corporation may apply to the department of commerce for senior citizen center infrastructure grants
12 under [section 3].
13 (2) Nonprofit corporations shall submit grant applications to the department of commerce in order
14 to be eligible for funding under [section 3].
15 (3) The department of commerce is authorized to adopt guidelines necessary to implement
16 [sections 3 through 5].
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Condition of grants -- disbursement of funds. (1) The disbursement of
19 grant funds for the projects chosen by the department of commerce pursuant to [section 3] is subject to the
20 following conditions:
21 (a) for grants in an amount of $25,000 or more, the grant recipient shall document the availability
22 of matching funds or in-kind contribution of assets with an appraised value from private sources representing at
23 least $1 in value for each $1 of the grant;
24 (b) the grant recipient shall execute a grant agreement with the department of commerce that
25 includes a project management plan and reporting requirements to track the outcomes of allocated grants; and
26 (c) the grant recipient shall satisfy other specific requirements considered necessary by the
27 department of commerce to accomplish the purpose of the project as evidenced by the application to the
28 department of commerce.
