1 (2) Projects must adhere to the design standards required by applicable regulations. Recipients of
2 program funds for projects that are not subject to any design standards must comply with generally accepted
3 industry standards.
4 (3) If actual project expenses are lower than the projected expense of the project, the department
5 of commerce shall reduce the amount of grant funds to be provided to grant recipients.
6
7 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Maximum state funding available -- for each project -- for each
8 county. (1) The amount of state funding allocated to entities within any individual county under [sections 3
9 through 5] may not exceed $350,000. No more than two applications may be funded in any one county.
10 (2) The amount of a grant to any single project may not exceed $250,000.
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Transfer of funds. By July 1, 2025, the state treasurer shall transfer $5
13 million from the general fund to the senior citizen center infrastructure account established in [section 2].
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Appropriation. There is appropriated $5 million from the senior citizen
16 center infrastructure account established in [section 2] to the department of commerce for the biennium
17 beginning July 1, 2025, for grants authorized in [sections 3 through 5]. Appropriations are authorized to
18 continue through the biennium beginning July 1, 2029.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 10. Termination. [This act] terminates June 30, 2031.
